&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whilst working in A&amp;E is extremely challenging, it can also be one of the most rewarding departments and this is reflected in the rates we offer. We are looking to recruit qualified Nurses with experience in Emergency care who are looking for Full time or flexible hours to work in our friendly community-minded hospital, easily accessible from London and the surrounding area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To join, you must:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Currently be registered with the NMC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Be eligible to work in the UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Pass an enhanced DBS check&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As mentioned above, we offer great rates, access to the NHS pension, free mandatory training and the support of a professional and friendly team from the moment you register with us. You can also book your shifts from the comfort of your own home with our online bookings system!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply with your CV now to join the StaffBank team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bank Partners are a leading provider of independent staffing bank management and outsourced staffing services providing workers to some of the largest trusts in the NHS. We have over 20 years experience in managing hospital banks and we take pride in the knowledge that we provide a high quality service to the trusts we represent, supplying them with workers across multiple specialism’s including Doctors, Nurses and Allied Health Professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
